Contrary to what Speaker Johnson said, this looming health care crisis—one of the most significant health care premium hikes in history and historic cuts to Medicaid—needs to be fixed now. 

According to the non-partisan @USCBO, if we wait until December instead of acting now to extend healthcare tax credits, 1.5 million more people will go uninsured.

@USCBO also says premiums will increase by 4% if Congress waits to act.

